CYSTIC
FIBROSIS
CYSTIC
FIBROSIS
HAS
BEEN
REGARDED
AS
A
DISEASE
OF
INFANTS
YET
WITH
IMPROVED
MANAGEMENT
A
HIGH
PERCENTAGE
OF
PATIENTS
HOW
SURVIVE
INTO
YOUNG
ADULTHOOD
IN
ADDITION
MILD
CASES
MAY
NOT
BE
DETECTED
UNTIL
LONG
AFTER
INFANCE
THE
OLDER
PATIENT
OFTEN
HAS
MINIMAL
SYMPTOMS
AND
THE
MAJORITY
ARE
SOCIALLY
ACTIVE
AND
PRODUCTIVE
